git stash
git stash list					                                    (to see stash list)
git stash apply stash@{n number}
git stash clear      							(to clear stash items)

when you want to undo file from staging area
git reset (filename)
git reset .
when you want to delete file from both staging and workspace area
git reset - -hard

git reset – before commit			(git reset command undo file from staging area to workspace)
git revert – after commit			(git revert command helps you undo an existing commit)
git revert <wrong commit id by using git log command>
i
(Type message manually please ignore previous commit)

How to remove untracked file
git clean –n  (dry run)
git clean –f (forcefully)

            Tagging
git tag –a <tag name> –m “xyz” <commit id>
git tag   						(to see the list of the tag)
git show <tag name>  				(to see particular commit content by using tag)
git tag –d <tag name>				(to delete a tag)
git  clone – git clone (url of the git hub repo)
Diffrence between git clone and git add

Git clone: It creates a local repo automatically in linux machine with the same name as in git hub.
Git add: In git add we need to make a local repo from our end only.

For files , we can use rm -f "filename"
For directory ,we can use rm -rf "dirname"


